<h2 id="guidelines">Guidelines</h2>
<h3 id="line-length">Characters per line</h3>
<p>It is recommend that lines of text be no more than <span class="fnt-bold">65-75 characters</span>, including spaces (<span
        class="fnt-italic">Designing
  With Type</span>, James Craig). This makes for a more comfortable reading experience. Usability studies dating back to the 1970's show readers experience fatigue with text running longer than this.</p>
<h3 id="seo">SEO</h3>
<p>Using text elements semantically improves SEO and accessibility.</p>
<h3 id="a11y">Accessibility</h3>
<p>The smallest font size that M- has is 13px, which is the smallest recommended by WCAG 2.1. Any smaller can be illegible for some users.</p>
